Missing one or two categories there.  The self buff damage shield one used by the likes of illusion: fire elemental, Call of Earth, and the Coldain Rings is one.  These stack and are meant to do so, always have.  Since there isn't a way to turn the tank into a fire elemental (too bad, that's a 16 point shield at 60), best you can do there is the 8 point from the coldain rings, I believe.  Also, unless I'm mistaken (don't play a dr00d, so could be), the druid's bramblecoat line stacks with this category as well as normal damage shields and potions, meaning it is is a category of it's own.  Self only buffs, but there are a few items that let tanks cast it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umnudge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mnudge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/4/02 8:25:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10525.topic&index=68>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Max Possible Damage Shield Damage...</span><hr size=1> There was nothing wrong with this post and no reason to change it's thread title to &quot;.&quot; jdoe.  I don't see why you succumbed to the pressure from people who want to keep secret every little exploit.  Who cares what they think?  Your original post wasn't made to cause a nerf (fix) and the thread itself has nothing to do with anything currently on test.  Dunno, but it seems an attempt to bury the post because the &quot;cool kids&quot; were complaining about their favorite sploits being discussed seems to be a misstep.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utanisemanasponge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanise Manasponge</A></span><br> <span 